In re Knut ELBERS, Christiane Meyer, Martina Von Freyburg, and Gregor Meyers. No. 2011-1286. United States Court of Appeals, Federal Circuit. Jan. 17, 2012. Julie A. Scott, Boehringer Ingelheim Vetmedica, Inc., of St. Joseph, Missouri, argued for appellant. Farheena Y. Rasheed, Associate Solicitor, United States Patent and Trademark Office, of Alexandria, VA, argued for appellee. With him on the brief were Raymond T. Chen, Solicitor, and Robert J. McManus, Associate Solicitor.

RADER, Chief Judge, O’MALLEY and REYNA, Circuit Judges.

JUDGMENT

PER CURIAM.

This Cause having been heard and considered, it is

Ordered and Adjudged:

AFFIRMED. See Fed. Cir. R. 36.
